Nigerian singer, Korede Bello, has stated that the issue of submission in relationships wasn’t gender sensitive. The singer made this known in a tweet, where he described submission as a ‘”two-way street.” According to Punch, the Godwin crooner, the word ‘submission’ was being used differently, adding that one should offer love and attention to their partner. The tweet read, “In every relationship, ‘submission’ is a two-way street. We just word(sic) it differently. “When you choose to be with a partner you’ve decided to submit your loyalty, attention, energy, service and love to that person. So submission is not gender-sensitive.”      Korede Bello After a long while, the Nigerian musician and songwriter, Korede Bello has taken to his timeline on Twitter to announce the date he is releasing his new single. Many people had previously believed Korede’s music career has come to an end after the hiphop artist has failed to… In "Entertainment" Popular Actress Iyabo, daughter Priscilla Ajoke Ojo was seen in a new love music video with Korede bello in short romantic tease. Gistvic Reports. Popular Nigerian singer, Korede Bello has decided to drop a new music titled "Mr Vendor" which would be dropping tomorrow as Priscilla Ajoke Ojo was seen… In "Entertainment" Lagos - Some Nigerians have continued to express their lack of confidence in the Nigeria Police in spite of the efforts by the Inspector-General of Police, Mr Solomon Arase, to rebrand it. Mavin records singer, Korede Bello, named the first ever Youth Ambassador of the force, shared a snippet video of a… In "Style"